casebody.data:
November 21, 1949.

Per Curiam Decisions.

No. 255,

October Term, 1948.

Eisler v. United States. Solicitor General Perlman was on the motion to dismiss for the United States. David Rein and Joseph Forer were on a memorandum opposing the motion for petitioner. Per Curiam:

The motion to dismiss is granted and the writ of certiorari is dismissed.

Mr. Justice Douglas and Mr. Justice Clark took no part in the consideration or decision of this case.
